4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH AND CELEBRATING THE LIFE OF ROBERT
5 CURTIS SKIDMORE.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that we note the
8 death on January 19, 2026, of Robert Curtis "Bobby"
9 Skidmore, of Citronelle, Alabama, at the age of 84; his
10 passing leaves a void in the lives of his loving family,
11 many friends, and the community in which he was highly
12 regarded; and
13 WHEREAS, Bobby Skidmore was born on January 22, 1941,
14 in Russellville, Alabama, to the union of Sallie and James
15 Skidmore; and
16 WHEREAS, he was a kind-hearted, gentle, and humble
17 man who was deeply devoted to his family, a loving and
18 faithful husband to his wife Betty, and someone who never
19 spoke an unkind word, thereby earning the respect and
20 affection of all who knew him; and
21 WHEREAS, throughout his life, Bobby Skidmore
22 demonstrated his love for God, family, and community through
23 faithful service; he dedicated many years as a youth
24 baseball coach; he was a devoted member of Cross Point
25 Baptist Church, where he taught an adult Sunday School class
26 for many years; and he was a gifted musician who shared his
27 talents by singing regularly in church and playing the
28 rhythm guitar; he also played in a high school performing
Page 1

rhythm guitar; he also played in a high school performing
HR104 INTRODUCED
29 band and greatly enjoyed singing karaoke; and
30 WHEREAS, Bobby Skidmore was an avid outdoorsman who
31 embraced life through hunting, fishing, camping, and
32 gardening; however, above all else, he loved the Lord and
33 cherished spending time with his family; and
34 WHEREAS, Bobby Skidmore was preceded in death by his
35 beloved wife, Betty Jean Sikes Skidmore; father, James
36 Curtis Skidmore; mother, Sallie Madden Skidmore; and
37 siblings, Larry Skidmore, Donnie Skidmore, Doris Brooks, and
38 Betty Sue Bavar; and
39 WHEREAS, he is survived by his sons, Barry Curtis
40 Skidmore (Tonya) and Byron Keith Skidmore (Becky);
41 grandchildren, Brandon Skidmore, Jerrod Skidmore (Patience),
42 Morgan Hinton (Kyle), and Avery Skidmore;
43 great-grandchildren, Jace Skidmore, Kennedy Skidmore,
44 Blakely Skidmore, Avery Hinton, Lane Hinton, and Brooks
45 Hinton; as well as a host of other loving family members and
46 friends; and
47 WHEREAS, although his presence will be greatly
48 missed, the memory of Bobby Skidmore will be cherished in
49 the hearts of all who knew and loved him; now therefore,
50 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
51 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of Robert Curtis
52 "Bobby" Skidmore is recorded with deep sadness, and this
53 resolution is offered in tribute to his life and service to
54 others, along with heartfelt sympathy to his family, whose
55 grief is shared by many.
